#. type: =head1
#: po4a:3 po4a-gettextize:3 po4a-normalize:3 po4a-translate:3 po4a-updatepo:3 msguntypot:3 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:3 lib/Locale/Po4a/Pod.pm:3 lib/Locale/Po4a/TransTractor.pm:24
msgid "SYNOPSIS"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:4
msgid "B<po4a> [I<options>] I<config_file>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:6
msgid ""
"po4a (PO for anything) eases the maintenance of the documentation's "
"translation using the classical gettext tools. To that extend, the main "
"feature of po4a is to decouple the translatable content of a document from "
"its structure."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:7
msgid ""
"When you run the B<po4a> program for the first time, with the master "
"documents only, it produces a POT file (also called translation catalog) "
"that contains all translatable strings of the document in a form that ease "
"the work of translators."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:8
msgid ""
"Such files can either be translated with a specific editor such as the "
"B<Gnome Translation Editor> or KDE's B<Lokalize>, or they can be integrated "
"in an online localization platform such as B<weblate> or B<pootle>. The "
"translation result is a set of PO files, one per language."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:9
msgid ""
"When you run the B<po4a> program with both the master documents and the PO "
"files, it produces the translated documents by injecting the content's "
"translation (found in the PO files) into the structure of the original "
"master document."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:10
msgid ""
"If the master documents changed in the meanwhile, po4a will update the PO "
"and POT files accordingly, so that the translators can easily detect the "
"modifications and update their work. Depending on your settings, po4a will "
"discard the partially translated documents, or produce a document mixing "
"English (for the new or modified paragraphs) and the target language (for "
"the paragraph which translation is already in the PO file)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:11
msgid ""
"By default, the translated documents are produced when at least 80% of their "
"content is translated (see the I<--keep> option below).  Discarding "
"translations as soon as they are not 100% may be discouraging for the "
"translators, while showing \"translation\" that are too partial may be "
"troubling for the end users."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:12
msgid ""
"You can mimic the behavior of the B<po4a> program with the other tools of "
"the suite (i.e., L<po4a-gettextize(1)>, L<po4a-updatepo(1)>, and "
"L<po4a-translate(1)>) using scripts and makefiles, but this quickly becomes "
"bothersome and repetitive. It is highly recommended to use the B<po4a> "
"program in your build script."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:14 po4a-translate:28
msgid "B<-k>, B<--keep>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:15
msgid ""
"Minimal threshold for translation percentage to keep (i.e. write) the "
"resulting file (default: 80). I.e. by default, files have to be translated "
"at least at 80% to be written on disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:16 po4a-gettextize:28 po4a-normalize:15 po4a-translate:32 po4a-updatepo:28
msgid "B<-h>, B<--help>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:17 po4a-gettextize:29 po4a-normalize:16 po4a-translate:33 po4a-updatepo:29
msgid "Show a short help message."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:18 po4a-gettextize:18 po4a-normalize:21 po4a-translate:18 po4a-updatepo:16
msgid "B<-M>, B<--master-charset>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:19
msgid ""
"Charset of the files containing the documents to translate. Note that all "
"master documents must use the same charset."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:20 po4a-gettextize:22 po4a-translate:22
msgid "B<-L>, B<--localized-charset>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:21
msgid ""
"Charset of the files containing the localized documents. Note that all "
"translated documents will use the same charset."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:22 po4a-translate:14
msgid "B<-A>, B<--addendum-charset>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:23 po4a-translate:15
msgid ""
"Charset of the addenda. Note that all the addenda should be in the same "
"charset."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:24 po4a-gettextize:32 po4a-normalize:27 po4a-translate:36 po4a-updatepo:32
msgid "B<-V>, B<--version>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:25 po4a-gettextize:33 po4a-normalize:28 po4a-translate:37 po4a-updatepo:33
msgid "Display the version of the script and exit."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:26 po4a-gettextize:34 po4a-translate:38 po4a-updatepo:34
msgid "B<-v>, B<--verbose>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:27 po4a-gettextize:35 po4a-translate:39 po4a-updatepo:35
msgid "Increase the verbosity of the program."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:28
msgid "B<-q>, B<--quiet>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:29
msgid "Decrease the verbosity of the program."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:30 po4a-gettextize:36 po4a-translate:40 po4a-updatepo:36
msgid "B<-d>, B<--debug>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:31 po4a-gettextize:37 po4a-translate:41 po4a-updatepo:37
msgid "Output some debugging information."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:32 po4a-gettextize:26 po4a-normalize:10 po4a-translate:26 po4a-updatepo:20
msgid "B<-o>, B<--option>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:33 po4a-gettextize:27 po4a-normalize:11 po4a-translate:27
msgid ""
"Extra option(s) to pass to the format plugin. Specify each option in the "
"'I<name>B<=>I<value>' format. See the documentation of each plugin for more "
"information about the valid options and their meanings."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:34
msgid "B<-f>, B<--force>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:35
msgid ""
"Always generate the POT and PO files, even if B<po4a> considers it is not "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:36
msgid "The default behavior (when B<--force> is not specified) is the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:37
msgid ""
"If the POT file already exists, it is regenerated if a master document or "
"the configuration file is more recent (unless B<--no-update> is provided).  "
"The POT file is also written in a temporary document and B<po4a> verifies "
"that the changes are really needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:38
msgid ""
"Also, a translation is regenerated only if its master document, the PO file, "
"one of its addenda or the configuration file is more recent.  To avoid "
"trying to regenerate translations which do not pass the threshold test (see "
"B<--keep>), a file with the F<.po4a-stamp> extension can be created (see "
"B<--stamp>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:39
msgid ""
"If a master document includes files, you should use the B<--force> flag "
"because the modification time of these included files are not taken into "
"account."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:40
msgid "The PO files are always re-generated based on the POT with B<msgmerge -U>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:41
msgid "B<--stamp>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:42
msgid ""
"Tells B<po4a> to create stamp files when a translation is not generated "
"because it does not reach the threshold. These stamp files are named "
"according to the expected translated document, with the F<.po4a-stamp> "
"extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:43
msgid ""
"Note: This only activates the creation of the F<.po4a-stamp> files. The "
"stamp files are always used if they exist, and they are removed with "
"B<--rm-translations> or when the file is finally translated."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:44
msgid "B<--no-translations>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:45
msgid "Do not generate the translated documents, only update the POT and PO files."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:46
msgid "B<--no-update>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:47
msgid "Do not change the POT and PO files, only the translation may be updated."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:48
msgid "B<--keep-translations>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:49
msgid ""
"Keeps the existing translation files even if the translation doesn't meet "
"the threshold specified by B<--keep>.  This option does not create new "
"translation files with few content, but it will save existing translations "
"which decay because of changes to the master files."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:50
msgid ""
"WARNING: This flag changes the po4a behavior in a rather drastic way: your "
"translated files will not get updated at all until the translation "
"improves. Only use this flag if you prefer shipping an outdated translated "
"documentation rather than only shipping an accurate untranslated "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:51
msgid "B<--rm-translations>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:52
msgid "Remove the translated files (implies B<--no-translations>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:53
msgid "B<--no-backups>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:54 po4a:56
msgid "This flag does nothing since 0.41, and may be removed in later releases."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:55
msgid "B<--rm-backups>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:57
msgid "B<--translate-only> I<translated-file>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:58
msgid ""
"Translate only the specified file.  It may be useful to speed up processing "
"if a configuration file contains a lot of files.  Note that this option does "
"not update PO and POT files.  This option can be used multiple times."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:59
msgid "B<--variable> I<var>B<=>I<value>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:60
msgid ""
"Define a variable that will be expanded in the B<po4a> configuration file.  "
"Every occurrence of I<$(var)> will be replaced by I<value>.  This option can "
"be used multiple times."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:61
msgid "B<--srcdir> I<SRCDIR>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:62
msgid ""
"Set the base directory for all input documents specified in the B<po4a> "
"configuration file. By default, PO files may be modified in I<srcdir>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:63
msgid ""
"With B<--no-update>, the PO files will not be updated at all, ensuring that "
"the content of I<srcdir> will remain untouched."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:64
msgid ""
"Another approach to prevent any modification of I<srcdir> is to specify a "
"I<destdir>: the updated PO files will be placed in I<destdir>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:65
msgid "B<--destdir> I<DESTDIR>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:66
msgid ""
"Set the base directory for all the output documents specified in the B<po4a> "
"configuration file. If B<destdir> is specified, all file modifications will "
"occur in this directory. Files existing out of this directory will be read "
"but not modified. Instead, a new version will be created in B<destdir>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:67
msgid "Options modifying the POT header"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:68 po4a-updatepo:38 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:14
msgid "B<--porefs> I<type>[,B<wrap>|B<nowrap>]"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:69 po4a-updatepo:39 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:15
msgid ""
"Specify the reference format. Argument I<type> can be one of B<never> to not "
"produce any reference, B<file> to only specify the file without the line "
"number, B<counter> to replace line number by an increasing counter, and "
"B<full> to include complete references (default: full)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:70 po4a-updatepo:40 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:16
msgid ""
"Argument can be followed by a comma and either B<wrap> or B<nowrap> "
"keyword.  References are written by default on a single line.  The B<wrap> "
"option wraps references on several lines, to mimic B<gettext> tools "
"(B<xgettext> and B<msgmerge>).  This option will become the default in a "
"future release, because it is more sensible.  The B<nowrap> option is "
"available so that users who want to keep the old behavior can do so."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:71 po4a-updatepo:41 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:17
msgid "B<--wrap-po> B<no>|B<newlines>|I<number> (default: 76)"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:72 po4a-updatepo:42 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:18
msgid ""
"Specify how the po file should be wrapped. This gives the choice between "
"either files that are nicely wrapped but could lead to git conflicts, or "
"files that are easier to handle automatically, but harder to read for "
"humans."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:73 po4a-updatepo:43 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:19
msgid ""
"Historically, the gettext suite has reformatted the po files at the 77th "
"column for cosmetics. This option specifies the behavior of po4a. If set to "
"a numerical value, po4a will wrap the po file after this column and after "
"newlines in the content. If set to B<newlines>, po4a will only split the "
"msgid and msgstr after newlines in the content. If set to B<no>, po4a will "
"not wrap the po file at all.  The wrapping of the reference comments is "
"controlled by the B<--porefs> option."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:74 po4a-updatepo:44 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:20
msgid ""
"Note that this option has no impact on how the msgid and msgstr are wrapped, "
"ie on how newlines are added to the content of these strings."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:75
msgid "B<-M>, B<--master-language>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:76
msgid ""
"Language of the source files containing the documents to translate. Note "
"that all master documents must use the same language."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:77 po4a-gettextize:38 po4a-updatepo:45 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:21
msgid "B<--msgid-bugs-address> I<email@address>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:78 po4a-gettextize:39 po4a-updatepo:46 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:22
msgid ""
"Set the report address for msgid bugs. By default, the created POT files "
"have no Report-Msgid-Bugs-To fields."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:79 po4a-gettextize:40 po4a-updatepo:47 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:23
msgid "B<--copyright-holder> I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:80 po4a-gettextize:41 po4a-updatepo:48 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:24
msgid ""
"Set the copyright holder in the POT header. The default value is \"Free "
"Software Foundation, Inc.\""
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:81 po4a-gettextize:42 po4a-updatepo:49 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:25
msgid "B<--package-name> I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:82 po4a-gettextize:43 po4a-updatepo:50 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:26
msgid "Set the package name for the POT header. The default is \"PACKAGE\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:83 po4a-gettextize:44 po4a-updatepo:51 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:27
msgid "B<--package-version> I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:84 po4a-gettextize:45 po4a-updatepo:52 lib/Locale/Po4a/Po.pm:28
msgid "Set the package version for the POT header. The default is \"VERSION\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:85
msgid "Options to modify the PO files"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:86 po4a-updatepo:26
msgid "B<--msgmerge-opt> I<options>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:87 po4a-updatepo:27
msgid "Extra options for B<msgmerge>(1)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:88
msgid "Note: B<$lang> will be extended to the current language."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:89 po4a-updatepo:22
msgid "B<--no-previous>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:90 po4a-updatepo:23
msgid ""
"This option removes B<--previous> from the options passed to B<msgmerge>.  "
"This permits to support versions of B<gettext> earlier than 0.16."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:91 po4a-updatepo:24
msgid "B<--previous>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:92 po4a-updatepo:25
msgid ""
"This option adds B<--previous> to the options passed to B<msgmerge>.  It "
"requires B<gettext> 0.16 or later, and is activated by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head1
#: po4a:93
msgid "DATA FLOWS"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:94
msgid ""
"The dataflow can be summarized as follow. Any changes to the master document "
"will be reflected in the PO files, and all changes to the PO files (either "
"manual or caused by previous step) will be reflected in translation "
"documents."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:95
msgid "Regular case where no B<pot_in> is specified:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:96
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" <- source files ->|<--------- build results --------------->\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:97
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" addendum ----------------------------------+\n"
"                                            |\n"
" master document --+---------------------+  |\n"
"                   V                     +--+--> translations\n"
" old PO files -----+--> updated PO files +  \n"
"      ^                      |\n"
"      |                      V\n"
"      +<.....................+\n"
"    (the updated PO files are manually\n"
"     copied to the source of the next\n"
"     release while manually updating\n"
"     the translation contents)\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:98
msgid ""
"Special case where a B<pot_in> is specified to filter the input master "
"document:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" <- source files ->|<--------- build results ----------------->\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" master document --+--------------------------+\n"
"                   :                          |\n"
" external          :    filtered              |\n"
" filtering ========X..> master                |\n"
" program                document              |\n"
"                        |                     |\n"
"                        V                     +--> translations\n"
" old PO files ----------+--> updated PO files +\n"
"      ^                           |\n"
"      |                           V\n"
"      +<..........................+\n"
"    (the updated PO files are manually\n"
"     copied to the source of the next\n"
"     release while manually updating\n"
"     the translation contents)\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:101
msgid ""
"The dataflow cannot be reversed in this tool, and changes in translations "
"are overwritten by the content of the PO files. As a matter of fact, this "
"tool cannot be used to convert existing translations to the po4a system. For "
"that task, please refer to L<po4a-gettextize(1)>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head1
#: po4a:102
msgid "CONFIGURATION FILE SYNTAX"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:103
msgid ""
"The (mandatory) argument is the path to the configuration file to use.  Its "
"syntax aims at being simple and close to the configuration files used by the "
"intl-tools projects."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:104
msgid ""
"Comments in these files are noted by the char '#'. It comments everything "
"until the end of the line. Lines can be continued by escaping the end of "
"line.  All non blank lines must begin with a [] command, followed by its "
"arguments.  (sound difficult said that way, but it is rather easy, I hope ;)"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:105
msgid "Specifying the template languages"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:106 po4a:111
msgid ""
"B<Note:> It is recommended to use B<[po_directory]> rather than "
"B<[po4a_langs]> and B<[po4a_paths]>.  See section B<Autodetection of the "
"paths and languages> below."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:107
msgid ""
"This is an optional command that can simplify the whole config file, and "
"will make it more scalable. You have to specify a list of the languages in "
"which you want to translate the documents. This is as simple as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po4a_langs] fr de\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:109
msgid ""
"This will enable you to expand B<$lang> to all the specified languages in "
"the rest of the config file."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:110
msgid "Specifying the paths to translator inputs"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:112
msgid ""
"First, you have to specify where the translator input files (I.E. the files "
"used by translators to do their job) are located. It can be done by such a "
"line:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po4a_paths] doc/l10n/project.doc.pot \\\n"
"              fr:doc/l10n/fr.po de:doc/l10n/de.po\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:114
msgid ""
"The command is thus B<[po4a_paths]>. The first argument is the path to the "
"POT file to use. All subsequent arguments are of the self-explanatory form:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:115
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <lang>:<path to the PO file for this lang>\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:116 po4a:139
msgid ""
"If you've defined the template languages, you can rewrite the line above "
"this way:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po4a_paths] doc/l10n/project.doc.pot $lang:doc/l10n/$lang.po\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:118
msgid ""
"You can also use B<$master> to refer to the document filename. In this case, "
"B<po4a> will use a split mode: one POT and one PO (for each language) will "
"be created for each document specified in the B<po4a> configuration file.  "
"See the B<Split mode> section."
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:119
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po4a_paths] doc/$master/$master.pot $lang:doc/$master/$lang.po\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:120
msgid "Autodetection of the paths and languages"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:121
msgid ""
"Another command can be used to specify the name of a directory where the PO "
"and POT files are located.  When it is used, B<po4a> will detect the POT "
"file as the only F<*.pot> file from the specified directory.  B<po4a> will "
"also use the list of F<*.po> files to define the list of languages (by "
"stripping out the extension).  These languages will be used for the "
"substitution of the B<$lang> variable in the rest of the configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:122
msgid ""
"This command should not be used together with the B<[po4a_langs]> or "
"B<[po4a_paths]> commands."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:123
msgid ""
"When using this command, you have to create an empty POT file on the first "
"invocation of B<po4a> to let it know the name of the POT file."
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po_directory] po4a/po/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:125
msgid "Specifying the documents to translate"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:126
msgid ""
"You now naturally have to specify which documents are translated, their "
"format, and where to put the translations. It can be made by such lines:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [type: sgml] doc/my_stuff.sgml fr:doc/fr/mon_truc.sgml \\\n"
"              de:doc/de/mein_kram.sgml\n"
" [type: pod] script fr:doc/fr/script.1 de:doc/de/script.1 \\\n"
"             add_fr:doc/l10n/script.fr.add\n"
" [type: docbook] doc/script.xml fr:doc/fr/script.xml \\\n"
"             de:doc/de/script.xml \\\n"
"             pot_in:doc/script.filtered.xml\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:128
msgid ""
"This should be rather self-explanatory also. Note that in the second case, "
"F<doc/l10n/script.fr.add> is an addendum to add to the French version of "
"this document.  Please refer to L<po4a(7)> for more information about the "
"addenda."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:129
msgid "More formally, the format is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:130
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [type: <format>] <master_doc> (<lang>:<localized_doc>)* \\\n"
"                  (pot_in:<filtered_master_doc>)? \\\n"
"                  (add_<lang>:<modifier>*<addendum_path>)*\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:131
msgid ""
"If B<pot_in> is specified, I<filtered_master_doc> is used to create POT file "
"instead of I<master_doc>.  This feature allows user to create flexible ways "
"to avoid contents which shouldn't be included in the PO files.  Tools such "
"as C preprocessor (B<cpp>) or XSL Transformation utility (e.g., B<xsltproc>) "
"can be used to create the external filtering program and call it before "
"invoking B<po4a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:132
msgid ""
"If there is no modifier, I<addendum_path> is a path to an addendum.  "
"Modifiers are"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:133
msgid "B<?>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:134
msgid "Include I<addendum_path> if this file does exist, otherwise do nothing."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:135
msgid "B<@>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:136
msgid ""
"I<addendum_path> is not a regular addendum but a file containing a list of "
"addenda, one by line.  Each addendum may be preceded by modifiers."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: po4a:137
msgid "B<!>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:138
msgid ""
"I<addendum_path> is discarded, it is not loaded and will not be loaded by "
"any further addendum specification."
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [type: pod] script $lang:doc/$lang/script.1 \\\n"
"             add_fr:doc/l10n/script.fr.add\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:141
msgid ""
"If all the languages had addenda with similar paths, you could also write "
"something like:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:142
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [type: pod] script $lang:doc/$lang/script.1 \\\n"
"             add_$lang:doc/l10n/script.$lang.add\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:143
msgid "Specifying options for the modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:144
msgid ""
"B<po4a> accepts options that will be passed to the module. These options are "
"module specific and are specified with the B<-o> switch."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:145
msgid ""
"If you need a specific option for one of the documents you want to "
"translate, you can also specify it in the configuration file. Options are "
"introduced by the B<opt> keyword. The argument of the B<opt> keyword must be "
"quoted with double quotes if it contains a space (e.g. if you specify "
"multiple options, or an option with an argument).  You can also specify "
"options that will only apply to a specific language by using the "
"B<opt_>I<lang> keyword."
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:146
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Here is an example:\n"
" [type:man] t-05-config/test02_man.1 $lang:tmp/test02_man.$lang.1 \\\n"
"            opt:\"-k 75\" opt_it:\"-L UTF-8\" opt_fr:-v\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:147
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Arguments may contain spaces if you use single quotes or escaped double\n"
"quotes:\n"
" [po4a_alias:man] man opt:\"-o \\\"mdoc=NAME,SEE ALSO\\\" -k 20\"\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:148
msgid ""
"If you want to specify the same options for many documents, you may want to "
"use an alias (see the B<Specifying aliases> section below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:149
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can also set options for all the documents specified in the\n"
"configuration file:\n"
" [options] opt:\"...\" opt_fr:\"...\"\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:150
msgid "Specifying aliases"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:151
msgid ""
"If you must specify the same options for multiple files, you may be "
"interested in defining a module alias. This can be done this way:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po4a_alias:test] man opt:\"-k 21\" opt_es:\"-o debug=splitargs\"\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:153
msgid ""
"This defines a module alias named B<test>, based on the B<man> module, with "
"the B<-k 21> applied to all the languages and with B<-o debug=splitargs> "
"applied to the Spanish translation."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:154
msgid "This module alias can then be used like a regular module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:155
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [type:test] t-05-config/test02_man.1 $lang:tmp/test02_man.$lang.1 \\\n"
"            opt_it:\"-L UTF-8\" opt_fr:-v\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:156
msgid "Note that you can specify additional options on a per file basis."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:157
msgid "Split mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:158
msgid "The split mode is used when B<$master> is used in the B<[po4a_paths]> line."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:159
msgid ""
"When the split mode is used, a temporary big POT and temporary big POs are "
"used. This permits to share the translations between all the POs."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:160
msgid ""
"If two POs have different translations for the same string, B<po4a> will "
"mark this string as fuzzy and will submit both translations in all the POs "
"which contain this string. Then, when a translator updates the translation "
"and removes the fuzzy tag in one PO, the translation of this string will be "
"updated in every POs automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:161
msgid ""
"If there are name conflicts because several files have the same filename, "
"the name of the master file can be specified by adding a "
"C<master:file=>I<name> option:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:162
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po4a_langs] de fr ja\n"
" [po4a_paths] l10n/po/$master.pot $lang:l10n/po/$master.$lang.po\n"
" [type: xml] foo/gui.xml $lang:foo/gui.$lang.xml master:file=foo-gui\n"
" [type: xml] bar/gui.xml $lang:bar/gui.$lang.xml master:file=bar-gui\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: po4a:163
msgid "EXAMPLE"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:164
msgid ""
"Let's assume you maintain a program named B<foo> which has a man page "
"F<man/foo.1> which naturally is maintained in English only. Now you as the "
"upstream or downstream maintainer want to create and maintain the "
"translation.  First you need to create the POT file necessary to send to "
"translators using L<po4a-gettextize(1)>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:165
msgid "So for our case we would call"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" cd man && po4a-gettextize -f man -m foo.1 -p foo.pot\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:167
msgid ""
"You would then send this file to the appropriate language lists or offer it "
"for download somewhere on your website."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:168
msgid ""
"Now let's assume you received three translations before your next release: "
"F<de.po> (including an addendum F<de.add>), F<sv.po> and F<pt.po>.  Since "
"you don't want to change your F<Makefile>(s) whenever a new translation "
"arrives you can use B<po4a> with an appropriate configuration file in your "
"F<Makefile>.  Let's call it F<po4a.cfg>. In our example it would look like "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:169
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [po_directory] man/po4a/po/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" [type: man] man/foo.1 $lang:man/translated/$lang/foo.1 \\\n"
"            add_$lang:?man/po4a/add_$lang/$lang.add opt:\"-k 80\"\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:171
msgid ""
"In this example we assume that your generated man pages (and all PO and "
"addenda files) should be stored in F<man/translated/$lang/> (respectively in "
"F<man/po4a/po/> and F<man/po4a/add_$lang/>) below the current directory. In "
"our example the F<man/po4a/po/> directory would include F<de.po>, F<pt.po> "
"and F<sv.po>, and the F<man/po4a/add_de/> directory would include F<de.add>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:172
msgid ""
"Note the use of the modifier B<?> as only the German translation (F<de.po>) "
"is accompanied by an addendum."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:173
msgid ""
"To actually build the translated man pages you would then (once!) add the "
"following line in the B<build> target of the appropriate F<Makefile>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:174
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        po4a po4a.cfg\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:175
msgid ""
"Once this is set up you don't need to touch the F<Makefile> when a new "
"translation arrives, i.e. if the French team sends you F<fr.po> and "
"F<fr.add> then you simply drop them respectively in F<man/po4a/po/> and "
"F<man/po4a/add_fr/> and the next time the program is built the French "
"translation is automatically build as well in F<man/translated/fr/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: po4a:176
msgid ""
"Note that you still need an appropriate target to install localized manual "
"pages with English ones."
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: po4a:177
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Finally if you do not store generated files into your version control "
"system,\n"
"you will need a line in your B<clean> target as well:\n"
"        -rm -rf man/translated\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

